## 1. Definitions

1.1. **“Licensed Work”**  
&emsp;The software (including any modifications or derivative works) distributed under this License by the Licensor, as specified above.

1.2. **“Licensee”**  
&emsp;An individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

1.3. **“Non-Production Use”**  
&emsp;Use of the Licensed Work for internal testing, development, research, experimentation, or other non-commercial activities — **excluding** any activity that provides services or software in a commercial, for-profit, or production environment.

1.4. **“Production Use”**  
&emsp;Any operation of the Licensed Work for commercial or for-profit purposes, including (but not limited to) providing paid services, or incorporating the Licensed Work into a commercial product or service that is accessed by end users or customers.

1.5. **“Change Date”**  
&emsp;Three (3) years from the Effective Date. After this date, the Additional Use Grant (Section 3.4) automatically applies.


